This feature begain its life as the DigitalOcean Poster Service (do_poster).  It's now being referred to by its other name, Skolr.

To build, clone the repo, and run the dependencies.make file using Drush Make.

1. clone the repo
2. make a drupal installation with all the necessary modules
3. enable the skolr module (legacy name: do_poster)

Example:

$ git clone git://github.com/ezwart/skolr.git
$ drush make skolr/dependencies.make drupal
$ cd drupal
$ drush en do_poster -y


 

